Did George HW Bush basically single-handedly destroy the USSR? If you assume he was the one actually running the show during the Reagan years. Like someone has to have made the case that the Bush family blew communism up and no one talks about it much.

Like if you just read the Wikipedia page without knowing anything else more "advanced" it seems the director of the CIA became VP to an actor with dementia and basically took control of and operated the entire state over two decades to annihilate their greatest geopolitical rival

I don't actually believe this but it just seems like the most straightforward normie explanation possible but you never see it articulated like this for some reason. Like no one *lionizes* George Bush but he was (possibly) calling the shots through the entire USSR collapse years.

Basically you often see "based Nixon", "LBJ was right", "Truman saved the USA", etc. but I have never seen anyone say "Based Bush" or anything of the sort, even normie conservatives never lionize him. Like the "Reagan era" is as far away from us as WW2 from them, time has passed.

I think it's because later his son's Dubya years were seen as embarassing and talking about the Bush family in general started to be seen as cringe and socially shamed so Reagan became a sort of "old school USA free world capitalism" personofied symbol even if he was just a face.
